# Architecture: Inverse Tree of Life

We flipped the pipeline. Normal compute: `bits → CPU → packets → deploy`.
Chromatic compute: `photons → SLM → interference → emit`.

## Mapping

| Sephirah | Stage | Physics | Code |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| 1 Kether | Absorb | Photodiode array | `kether_absorb()` |
| 2 Chokhmah | Diffract | Grating → 5 bands | `chokhmah_diffract()` |
| 3 Binah | Filter | Dichroic policy | `binah_filter()` |
| 6 Tiphareth | Interfere | SLM hologram | `tiphareth_interfere()` |
| 9 Yesod | Guide | λ→angle routing | `yesod_guide()` |
| 10 Malkuth | Emit | Laser diodes | `malkuth_emit()` |

## Data Model

Packet = `Spectrum(bands, phase)`
`bands`: np.array([UV,B,G,R,IR]) power in mW
`phase`: np.array(64,64) SLM phase map

Routing: `np.argmax(bands)` + `mean(phase[quadrant])` → neighbor

## Consensus

No blockchain. Phase-locking between SLMs. If your laser is incoherent, neighbors drop you. Gevurah = bandpass filter rejecting unauthorized spectrum.

## Path of Return

Backscatter sensors read reflected power. Gradient descent on `slm_state` minimizes loss. This is TCP ACK but with light.